            <p>
                Human Resource Management (HRM) plays a vital role in building a productive, compliant, and engaged workforce. A modern HR management system helps organizations streamline people operations, reduce manual work, and improve employee experience.
                In this article, we explore the top 10 functions of a Human Resource Management System and how they support business growth.
            </p>
            <!-- Start New Section -->
            <div class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">1. Employee Information Management</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text">
                    Employee Information Management is the core function of an HRMS. It maintains a centralized database of employee personal details, job roles, department information, documents, and employment history. This allows quick access to accurate data, improves security, reduces paperwork, and ensures smooth HR operations.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="article-section2">
                <h2 class="section-title2">2. Recruitment and Onboarding</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card2">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle 2.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text2">
                    This function manages the complete hiring process, from job posting to candidate selection. The HRMS tracks applications, schedules interviews, and simplifies onboarding by collecting documents, assigning roles, and sharing company policies, ensuring a smooth start for new employees.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="article-section3">
                <h2 class="section-title3">3. Attendance and Leave Management</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card3">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle3.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text3">
                    Attendance and Leave Management automates the tracking of employee working hours, overtime, holidays, and leave balances. It reduces manual errors, improves transparency, and ensures accurate payroll processing while helping employees easily apply for and track leave.
                </p>
            </div>
             <div class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">4. Payroll Management</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card4">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle 4.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text">
                    Payroll Management ensures accurate and timely salary processing by automating calculations, deductions, bonuses, and tax components. The HRMS generates payslips, maintains payroll records, and supports compliance with local payroll regulations, saving time and reducing errors.
                </p>
            </div>
             <div class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">5. Performance Management</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card5">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle 5.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text">
                    This function supports employee performance evaluation through goal setting, reviews, and feedback. The HRMS enables managers to track progress, identify skill gaps, and recognize high performers, improving productivity and employee engagement.
                </p>
            </div>
             <div class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">6.Training and Development</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card6">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle 6.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text">

                    Training and Development modules help organizations plan and manage employee learning programs.
                    The HRMS tracks training schedules, attendance, skill development, and certifications, supporting
                    continuous workforce improvement and long-term growth.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">7. Compliance and Policy Management</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card7">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle 7.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text">
                    Compliance and Policy Management helps organizations follow labor laws, internal rules, and company policies.
                    The HRMS stores policy documents, tracks acknowledgments, and maintains compliance records, reducing legal risks and ensuring transparency.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">8. Employee Self-Service (ESS)</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card8">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle 8.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text">
                    Employee Self-Service allows employees to access HR information independently.
                    Through ESS portals, employees can view payslips, apply for leave, update personal details,
                    and access company announcements, reducing HR workload and improving satisfaction.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">9. Reporting and HR Analytics</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card9">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle 9.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text">
                    The HRMS provides real-time reports and analytics on attendance, payroll, turnover, and performance.
                    These insights help HR teams and management make data-driven decisions and improve organizational efficiency.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title">10. Exit and Offboarding Management</h2>

                <div class="content-image-card10">
                    <!-- Image link -->
                    <img src="/image/blog circle 10.png" alt="Employee Information Management">
                </div>

                <p class="section-text">
                    Exit and Offboarding Management handles resignations, notice periods, final settlements, and exit documentation.
                    The HRMS ensures a structured offboarding process, maintains records, and supports compliance while preserving a positive employee experience.
                </p>
            </div>
